1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

* **Count & Layers:** The structure uses 7 blocks.  There are two distinct sections. One has three layers, and the other has two.

* **Spatial Relationships:**
    * **Section 1 (Left):** A red block with a hole (index 1) forms the base. A blue cube (index 3) is placed inside the hole. Another red block (index 4) sits on top of the first red block, partially covering the blue cube.
    * **Section 2 (Right):** Two orange cylinders (index 8) are placed side-by-side. A yellow block (index 5) sits atop these cylinders. Another yellow block (index 6) rests horizontally on top of the first yellow block. A single taller orange cylinder (index 8) is placed vertically beside the other two, forming a tower.
